## 🎨 **Landing Page Style System (Cyber Carrot)**

### **Overview**

The landing page uses a distinct style system optimized for marketing and conversion, while maintaining consistency with the overall Cyber Carrot Design System foundation. This section documents when and how to use landing page styles vs. webapp styles.

**See Also:**

- `docs/LANDING_PAGE_STYLE_GUIDE.md` - Complete landing page style guide
- `lib/landing-styles.ts` - Centralized landing page style utilities
- `docs/LANDING_STYLE_MIGRATION.md` - Migration guide for applying landing styles

### **When to Use Landing Page Styles**

**Use Landing Page Styles For:**

- ✅ Marketing pages (`/`, `/pricing`, `/features`, etc.)
- ✅ Public-facing content (landing pages, marketing sections)
- ✅ Conversion-focused components (CTAs, hero sections, feature showcases)
- ✅ Marketing emails and promotional content
- ✅ Public documentation pages

**Use Webapp Styles For:**

- ✅ Authenticated webapp pages (`/webapp/**`)
- ✅ Data-heavy interfaces (tables, forms, dashboards)
- ✅ Internal tools and admin interfaces
- ✅ Functional components (navigation, settings, data management)

**Decision Tree:**

1. Is this a public marketing page? → Use landing page styles
2. Is this an authenticated webapp page? → Use webapp styles
3. Is this a conversion-focused component? → Use landing page styles
4. Is this a data management interface? → Use webapp styles

### **Webapp Landing Style Integration**

**Hybrid Approach:** Landing page styles enhance user-facing elements (headers, CTAs, empty states) while Cyber Carrot Design System remains the default for data interfaces (tables, forms, dashboards).

**When to Use Landing Styles in Webapp:**

- ✅ **Page Headers** - Use `PageHeader` with `useLandingStyles={true}`
- ✅ **Navigation** - Breadcrumbs and user info in `NavigationHeader`
- ✅ **CTAs and Action Buttons** - Primary conversion-focused buttons
- ✅ **Empty States** - User guidance and onboarding
- ✅ **Quick Actions** - Dashboard action cards
- ✅ **Welcome Sections** - Feature introductions

**When to Use Cyber Carrot Design System in Webapp:**

- ✅ **Data Tables** - All table components
- ✅ **Forms** - Input fields, selects, checkboxes
- ✅ **Dashboards** - Data visualization and analytics
- ✅ **Modals** - Dialog boxes and overlays
- ✅ **Toasts** - Notification messages
- ✅ **Settings Pages** - Configuration interfaces

**Webapp Landing Style Resources:**

- [Webapp Landing Style Usage Guide](docs/WEBAPP_LANDING_STYLE_USAGE.md)
- [Webapp Style Decision Helpers](lib/webapp-styles.ts)
- [Landing Styles Utility File](lib/landing-styles.ts) - Includes `WEBAPP_LANDING_PRESETS` and helper functions

**Component Usage Examples:**

```tsx
// PageHeader with landing styles
<PageHeader
  title="Recipes"
  subtitle="Manage your recipe collection"
  useLandingStyles={true}
/>

// Button with landing styles
<Button
  variant="primary"
  landingStyle={true}
  magnetic={true}
  glow={true}
  onClick={handleClick}
>
  Add Recipe
</Button>

// EmptyState component
<EmptyState
  title="No recipes found"
  message="Start by creating your first recipe"
  icon={Plus}
  useLandingStyles={true}
  variant="landing"
  animated={true}
/>
```

**Style Decision Helpers:**

```tsx
import {
  shouldUseLandingStyles,
  getComponentStyleVariant,
  getAnimationConfig,
} from '@/lib/webapp-styles';

// Check if component should use landing styles
const useLanding = shouldUseLandingStyles('header', { userFacing: true });

// Get recommended style variant
const variant = getComponentStyleVariant('cta', { userFacing: true });

// Get animation configuration
const animConfig = getAnimationConfig('emptyState', { userFacing: true });
```

