### **Landing Page Typography**

**Fluid Typography System:**

The landing page uses fluid typography classes that scale smoothly across all screen sizes:

- `.text-fluid-xs` - Small captions (clamp(0.625rem, 1.4vw, 0.75rem))
- `.text-fluid-sm` - Body text, labels (clamp(0.875rem, 1.6vw, 1rem))
- `.text-fluid-base` - Standard body text (clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.125rem))
- `.text-fluid-lg` - Large body text (clamp(1.125rem, 2.4vw, 1.25rem))
- `.text-fluid-xl` - Section headers (clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.5rem))
- `.text-fluid-2xl` - Large headers (clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2rem))
- `.text-fluid-3xl` - Hero subheadings (clamp(1.875rem, 5vw, 2.5rem))
- `.text-fluid-4xl` - Hero headlines (clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, 3.5rem))

**Typography Hierarchy:**

- **Hero Headlines:** `text-fluid-4xl` with `font-bold` and `tracking-tight`
- **Section Headers:** `text-fluid-2xl` or `text-fluid-3xl` with `font-bold`
- **Body Text:** `text-fluid-base` or `text-fluid-lg` with `text-gray-400`
- **Captions:** `text-fluid-sm` or `text-fluid-xs` with `text-gray-500`

**Usage:**

- Always use fluid typography classes for landing page content
- Combine with responsive breakpoints for fine-tuning: `text-fluid-2xl tablet:text-fluid-3xl`
- Use `font-light` for hero sections, `font-bold` for emphasis

### **Landing Page Components**

#### **MagneticButton**

**Location:** `components/ui/MagneticButton.tsx`

**Purpose:** Interactive button with magnetic hover effect for enhanced engagement

**Props:**

- `strength?: number` - Magnetic pull strength (default: 0.3)
- `maxDistance?: number` - Maximum pull distance in pixels (default: 20)
- `scaleOnHover?: boolean` - Enable scale animation on hover (default: true)
- `hoverScale?: number` - Scale factor on hover (default: 1.05)

**Usage:**

```typescript
import { MagneticButton } from '@/components/ui/MagneticButton';

<MagneticButton
  className="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#29E7CD] to-[#D925C7] rounded-2xl px-8 py-4"
  onClick={handleClick}
>
  Get Started
</MagneticButton>
```

**When to Use:**

- Primary CTAs on landing pages
- Conversion-focused buttons
- Hero section actions
- Feature call-to-actions

**When NOT to Use:**

- Webapp functional buttons (use standard Button component)
- Form submissions (use standard form buttons)
- Navigation links (use Link component)

#### **GlowCard**

**Location:** `components/ui/GlowCard.tsx`

**Purpose:** Card component with radial gradient glow effect following mouse cursor

**Props:**

- `glowColor?: string` - RGBA color for glow effect (default: primary color)
- `glowIntensity?: number` - Glow intensity multiplier (default: 1.0)

**Usage:**

```typescript
import { GlowCard } from '@/components/ui/GlowCard';

<GlowCard glowColor="rgba(41, 231, 205, 0.15)" className="p-8">
  <h3>Feature Title</h3>
  <p>Feature description</p>
</GlowCard>
```

**When to Use:**

- Feature showcase cards
- Highlight sections
- Testimonial cards
- Metric displays

**When NOT to Use:**

- Data tables (use standard table styling)
- Form containers (use standard card styling)
- Webapp dashboard cards (use Cyber Carrot Design System cards)

#### **ScrollReveal**

**Location:** `components/ui/ScrollReveal.tsx`

**Purpose:** Animates children into view as they scroll into viewport

**Props:**

- `variant?: 'fade-up' | 'fade-in' | 'scale-up' | 'slide-left' | 'slide-right'` - Animation type
- `delay?: number` - Animation delay in seconds
- `duration?: number` - Animation duration in seconds
- `offset?: number` - Viewport offset trigger (0-1)
- `once?: boolean` - Animate only once (default: true)

**Usage:**

```typescript
import { ScrollReveal } from '@/components/ui/ScrollReveal';

<ScrollReveal variant="fade-up" delay={0.2}>
  <h2>Section Title</h2>
</ScrollReveal>
```

**When to Use:**

- Landing page sections
- Feature introductions
- Testimonial reveals
- CTA sections

**When NOT to Use:**

- Webapp data loading (use LoadingSkeleton)
- Form fields (no animation needed)
- Navigation elements (use standard transitions)

